---
# ============================================================================
# ALL CONFIGURATION IS IN vault.yml (ENCRYPTED)
# ============================================================================
# This file is intentionally empty.  All deployment variables — identity,
# credentials, tuning, infrastructure sizing, and computed paths — live in
# vault.yml so the encrypted file can be committed to git.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Copy vault.yml.example to vault.yml
#   2. Fill in your values
#   3. Encrypt: ansible-vault encrypt group_vars/vault.yml --vault-password-file ~/.vault_pass
#
# Edit configuration:
#   ansible-vault edit group_vars/vault.yml --vault-password-file ~/.vault_pass
#
# View configuration:
#   ansible-vault view group_vars/vault.yml --vault-password-file ~/.vault_pass
# ============================================================================
